# Keep secrets and runtime state OUT of the build context (Dockerfile does `COPY . .`).
# Fix-SEC: without this, the gitignored real .env (JWT_SECRET, DB/MinIO creds, SEED_PASSWORD) and
# local state bake into every image — leaked the instant an image is pushed/saved (`docker history`).
# .env is supplied at RUNTIME via compose `env_file:`, so excluding it here does not affect boot.
#
# DO NOT add: requirements.lock (Dockerfile:23 installs it), docker-entrypoint.sh / worker-entrypoint.sh,
# app/, scripts/, alembic*, tests/ (the plugin-free suite is expected to run on the built image).

# secrets
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# runtime state (mounted as volumes at runtime, never baked)
state/
data/

# python / tooling caches
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
.pytest_cache/
.ruff_cache/
.mypy_cache/
htmlcov/
.coverage
*.log

# vcs / editor
.git/
.gitignore
.vscode/
.idea/
